and sexy.

62
00:05:48.912 --> 00:05:51.034
Save some energy for me.

63
00:05:51.034 --> 00:05:53.154
Wait for me at home if you're bored.

64
00:05:53.154 --> 00:05:55.113
<i>It's boring being alone there.</i>

65
00:05:55.113 --> 00:05:57.287
When I'm bored, you're busy.

66
00:05:57.287 --> 00:05:59.989
When you're bored, I'm busy.

67
00:06:00.473 --> 00:06:02.873
We don't get along, do we?

68
00:06:02.873 --> 00:06:05.095
How come we don't get along?

69
00:06:05.095 --> 00:06:07.063
I'll bring something delicious to rehearsal.

70
00:06:07.063 --> 00:06:08.298
Oh really?

71
00:06:08.298 --> 00:06:09.343
I'd love to.

72
00:06:09.343 --> 00:06:11.222
What do you want to eat?

73
00:06:11.222 --> 00:06:13.963
Meat. I want to eat until I burst.

74
00:06:13.963 --> 00:06:16.574
Okay, wait for me there.

75
00:06:16.574 --> 00:06:18.441
I love you.

76
00:06:37.901 --> 00:06:39.762
What the hell?

77
00:06:40.998 --> 00:06:43.000
The effort is noticeable in the environment.

78
00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:43.900
- What is it?
- What is it?

79
00:06:43.900 --> 00:06:45.435
Hello!

80
00:06:45.435 --> 00:06:46.734
- They are working a lot.
- Hello.

81
00:06:46.734 --> 00:06:47.801
Hello, how are you?

82
00:06:47.801 --> 00:06:49.673
I don't give more, it weighs. Grab this.

83
00:06:49.673 --> 00:06:51.534
What is it?

84
00:06:51.534 --> 00:06:53.643
Some lunch boxes.

85
00:06:54.233 --> 00:06:56.412
<i>Who the hell is this guy?</i>

86
00:06:59.883 --> 00:07:01.885
- It's very rich.
- Thank you.

87
00:07:01.885 --> 00:07:05.421
- Enjoy your food.
- Thanks for the food.

88
00:07:05.421 --> 00:07:06.757
What's that?

89
00:07:06.757 --> 00:07:08.792
- Steak!
- What are you doing here?

90
00:07:08.792 --> 00:07:10.961
What is this? You didn't even call.

91
00:07:10.961 --> 00:07:13.262
It's a surprise.

92
00:07:13.262 --> 00:07:16.164
Why do you do this?

93
00:07:16.164 --> 00:07:17.861
- It's delicious.
- To impress you, of course.

94
00:07:17.861 --> 00:07:18.535
Meat!

95
00:07:18.535 --> 00:07:21.400
That's why I bought all this and came.

96
00:07:21.400 --> 00:07:23.773
- Meat!
- What's that?

97
00:07:48.365 --> 00:07:51.168
[Eternal Love]

98
00:08:13.156 --> 00:08:16.493
<i>The teacher called me suddenly.
I don't think I can go.</i>

99
00:08:16.493 --> 00:08:18.327
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

100
00:08:22.299 --> 00:08:23.915
Your food got cold.

101
00:08:23.915 --> 00:08:24.816
What will you do next?

102
00:08:24.816 --> 00:08:27.771
What do you care?

103
00:08:27.771 --> 00:08:28.922
Won't you go to the office?

104
00:08:28.922 --> 00:08:30.086
I did my job

105
00:08:30.086 --> 00:08:31.275
and I came to see you.

106
00:08:31.275 --> 00:08:33.241
How do you know when I'm done?

107
00:08:33.241 --> 00:08:34.862
I leave work very late.

108
00:08:34.862 --> 00:08:36.801
I have all the time in the world

109
00:08:36.801 --> 00:08:38.948
for you.

110
00:08:41.018 --> 00:08:42.786
Eat something.

111
00:08:42.786 --> 00:08:44.342
I bought it for you.

112
00:08:44.342 --> 00:08:46.520
At least eat a little for commitment.

113
00:08:46.520 --> 00:08:47.791
Come on, choose.

114
00:08:47.791 --> 00:08:50.427
There are three combinations here. There are all kinds.

115
00:08:50.427 --> 00:08:52.141
<i>Are you going to cook?</i>

116
00:08:52.141 --> 00:08:53.330
<i>Are you alone?</i>

117
00:08:53.330 --> 00:08:55.098
<i>Your salad is burning.</i>

118
00:08:55.098 --> 00:08:56.987
I know, but here I am, cooking.

119
00:08:56.987 --> 00:09:01.906
I begged you not to do it and I insulted him,

120
00:09:01.906 --> 00:09:05.775
Now they will come out again and you will give yourself to him?

121
00:09:05.775 --> 00:09:08.434
You said being alone was the most comfortable.

122
00:09:08.434 --> 00:09:10.047
You said that all men are equal,

123
00:09:10.047 --> 00:09:11.934
but to see the good in them.

124
00:09:11.934 --> 00:09:14.414
<i>Did you find any virtue?</i>

125
00:09:14.414 --> 00:09:17.167
I could sense them without even looking at it.

126
00:09:17.167 --> 00:09:21.558
I felt bad thinking about how difficult
which was for him.

127
00:09:21.558 --> 00:09:24.161
It's touching
see him try to take responsibility.

128
00:09:24.161 --> 00:09:26.879
<i>You ignore your friend from 20 years ago</i>

129
00:09:26.879 --> 00:09:30.398
<i>because you fell madly in love with him.</i>

130
00:09:30.398 --> 00:09:33.503
And to lift his spirits and console him,

131
00:09:33.503 --> 00:09:36.719
You're going to do the apron act.

132
00:09:36.719 --> 00:09:38.375
Are you crazy? That's very childish.

133
00:09:38.375 --> 00:09:39.318
<i>Why?</i>

134
00:09:39.318 --> 00:09:42.258
It would be if someone else saw it,

135
00:09:42.258 --> 00:09:44.047
but it's just you two.

136
00:09:44.047 --> 00:09:46.216
If you're going to do it, do it well.

137
00:09:46.216 --> 00:09:47.618
<i>He said it's his fantasy.</i>

138
00:09:47.618 --> 00:09:48.838
<i>Who knows?</i>

139
00:09:48.838 --> 00:09:50.519
It would be a good opportunity

140
00:09:50.519 --> 00:09:53.456
for reunion sex.

141
00:10:03.266 --> 00:10:04.334
No!

142
00:10:04.334 --> 00:10:05.876
What am I thinking about?

143
00:10:05.876 --> 00:10:07.637
No.

144
00:10:08.338 --> 00:10:09.776
Not that.

145
00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:11.674
Of course not.

146
00:10:13.243 --> 00:10:15.312
Cut the potatoes into cubes.

147
00:10:15.312 --> 00:10:17.580
That's it.

148
00:10:25.655 --> 00:10:27.658
Jun Kyung.

149
00:10:27.658 --> 00:10:28.959
Jun Kyung.

150
00:10:28.959 --> 00:10:30.860
Surprise!

151
00:10:44.645 --> 00:10:46.809
Dad, where is the luggage?

152
00:11:10.701 --> 00:11:14.637
You should have told me you were coming with him.

153
00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:19.234
you should have told me

154
00:11:19.234 --> 00:11:21.334
that you were going to wait for me like this.

155
00:11:21.334 --> 00:11:22.997
What a shame.

156
00:11:22.997 --> 00:11:24.381
That curry you made

157
00:11:24.381 --> 00:11:26.415
It smelled delicious.

158
00:11:27.518 --> 00:11:30.052
He is very shy with strangers.

159
00:11:30.052 --> 00:11:33.656
Anyone would be shy after seeing me like this.

160
00:11:33.656 --> 00:11:35.938
I am condemned. What a bad first impression!

161
00:11:35.938 --> 00:11:37.860
Still,

162
00:11:38.434 --> 00:11:39.537
thank you.

163
00:11:39.537 --> 00:11:42.231
Oh really?

164
00:11:42.231 --> 00:11:43.700
I'll invite you home when I organize it.

165
00:11:43.700 --> 00:11:46.203
You will be able to greet Daniel properly.

166
00:11:46.203 --> 00:11:48.637
They're going to get along very quickly.

167
00:11:55.285 --> 00:11:57.334
Daniel.

168
00:11:57.334 --> 00:11:59.582
Bye bye.

169
00:12:22.038 --> 00:12:26.222
[Guide]

170
00:12:28.979 --> 00:12:31.314
<i>What would become of me</i>

171
00:12:31.848 --> 00:12:36.085
<i>without you?</i>

172
00:12:39.689 --> 00:12:41.824
<i>How would I make a living</i>

173
00:12:42.400 --> 00:12:45.060
<i>without you?</i>

174
00:12:59.849 --> 00:13:02.144
I have been...

175
00:13:02.934 --> 00:13:05.147
with another woman.

176
00:13:06.100 --> 00:13:09.251
In your heart?

177
00:13:10.287 --> 00:13:12.321
In my heart...

178
00:13:14.434 --> 00:13:16.692
and physically.

179
00:13:18.234 --> 00:13:21.866
Do you have a husband?

180
00:13:21.866 --> 00:13:25.367
He also passed away long ago.

181
00:13:25.367 --> 00:13:27.903
Do you love each other?

182
00:13:31.075 --> 00:13:32.642
Well...

183
00:13:33.412 --> 00:13:36.178
If feeling like this is loving yourself...

184
00:13:40.634 --> 00:13:42.718
So, yeah, maybe.

185
00:13:46.256 --> 00:13:49.158
So what's the problem?

186
00:13:52.366 --> 00:13:54.234
This situation

187
00:13:54.234 --> 00:13:57.199
It is very confusing and painful.

188
00:13:58.001 --> 00:14:01.337
I feel like I have an adventure.

189
00:14:03.400 --> 00:14:06.742
It's like I did something bad to him.
to the mother of my children.

190
00:14:11.400 --> 00:14:13.682
The place is busy.

191
00:14:17.755 --> 00:14:19.555
Please come out.

192
00:14:20.068 --> 00:14:22.024
Father, why...?

193
00:14:29.272 --> 00:14:34.003
Julia went with God.
How can you call that an adventure?

194
00:14:34.467 --> 00:14:36.705
Still, father.

195
00:14:36.705 --> 00:14:39.241
Call me Chang Sik.

196
00:14:40.330 --> 00:14:42.645
How could I address a priest like that?

197
00:14:44.481 --> 00:14:47.784
I'm the Sunday school troublemaker
from 20 years ago, Chang Sik.

198
00:14:47.784 --> 00:14:50.387
They caught me smoking,

199
00:14:50.387 --> 00:14:53.856
and you scolded me for chasing Jun Kyung.

200
00:14:54.670 --> 00:14:56.625
It doesn't matter.

201
00:14:58.495 --> 00:15:01.230
You are still as disconcerting as ever.

202
00:15:03.400 --> 00:15:05.202
Jin Ho,

203
00:15:05.202 --> 00:15:07.970
What are you so afraid of?

204
00:15:10.774 --> 00:15:12.490
My children's mother left recently.

205
00:15:12.490 --> 00:15:14.569
And how long is the right time?

206
00:15:14.569 --> 00:15:16.089
¿Six months?

207
00:15:16.089 --> 00:15:18.080
One year?

208
00:15:18.681 --> 00:15:20.517
Do you think Julia

209
00:15:20.517 --> 00:15:23.485
Would I want you to wallow alone in misery?

210
00:15:23.485 --> 00:15:26.790
If you had died first,
Would you have wanted that for her?

211
00:15:26.790 --> 00:15:28.769
-Chang Sik.
- Yeah.

212
00:15:28.769 --> 00:15:30.261
¡No!

213
00:15:30.261 --> 00:15:32.261
Padre.

214
00:15:34.498 --> 00:15:36.198
Chang Sik,

215
00:15:36.770 --> 00:15:38.668
do you find it pathetic

216
00:15:38.668 --> 00:15:40.591
to come all this way to confess something like that?

217
00:15:40.591 --> 00:15:44.130
You know our brothers and sisters.

218
00:15:44.130 --> 00:15:48.144
They come to speak ill of their spouses.

219
00:15:48.144 --> 00:15:50.513
They suspect, they fight

220
00:15:50.513 --> 00:15:52.316
and they repent,

221
00:15:52.316 --> 00:15:53.750
It's always the same story.

222
00:15:53.750 --> 00:15:55.318
Clear.

223
00:15:55.318 --> 00:15:57.367
When I hear your confessions,

224
00:15:57.367 --> 00:15:59.220
I feel like a marriage counselor,

225
00:15:59.220 --> 00:16:01.970
not a priest.

226
00:16:01.970 --> 00:16:05.928
Why do they bring you their relationship problems?
to a man who lives alone?

227
00:16:07.564 --> 00:16:10.633
It must be difficult for you too.

228
00:16:12.635 --> 00:16:16.172
You don't have to feel guilt.

229
00:16:16.172 --> 00:16:18.434
love someone

230
00:16:18.434 --> 00:16:19.502
It's a blessing.

231
00:16:19.502 --> 00:16:22.911
I know, but...

232
00:16:25.167 --> 00:16:26.402
what will others think?

233
00:16:26.402 --> 00:16:29.252
What does it matter what other people think?

234
00:16:29.252 --> 00:16:31.020
Because...?

235
00:16:31.822 --> 00:16:34.090
Why are you angry?

236
00:16:53.095 --> 00:16:55.210
Lord,

237
00:16:55.210 --> 00:16:58.021
thank you for guiding me along the path of an apostle

238
00:16:58.021 --> 00:17:00.368
and for letting me escape the yoke of marriage.

239
00:17:00.368 --> 00:17:05.454
It's a tedious link
that people can't break,

240
00:17:05.454 --> 00:17:08.557
even after one of them has died.

241
00:17:12.068 --> 00:17:13.922
Amen.

242
00:17:28.200 --> 00:17:30.167
I'll get you a fork.

243
00:17:30.167 --> 00:17:32.382
No, it's okay.

244
00:17:32.382 --> 00:17:35.651
I want to learn to use chopsticks.

245
00:17:54.534 --> 00:17:56.572
Let me see.

246
00:18:00.943 --> 00:18:03.634
This one here.

247
00:18:03.634 --> 00:18:06.081
Use these two fingers.

248
00:18:06.868 --> 00:18:09.218
- I see.
- So.

249
00:18:17.581 --> 00:18:19.841
<i>Have you had dinner yet?</i>

250
00:18:23.700 --> 00:18:26.543
<i>I'm eating curry.</i>

251
00:18:26.543 --> 00:18:29.372
<i>I had a craving
when you said you were cooking that.</i>

252
00:18:29.372 --> 00:18:31.440
Su Jin.

253
00:18:33.233 --> 00:18:36.111
How am I going to eat all this?

254
00:18:39.383 --> 00:18:41.583
Thank you.

255
00:18:42.997 --> 00:18:44.987
Why do you thank me?

256
00:18:45.457 --> 00:18:47.556
I am the grateful one.

257
00:18:51.327 --> 00:18:54.196
Everything is...

258
00:18:55.399 --> 00:18:57.332
difficult at first.

259
00:18:58.269 --> 00:19:00.235
It's uncomfortable.

260
00:19:01.639 --> 00:19:03.572
Eat.

261
00:19:07.960 --> 00:19:10.445
- Dad.
- Yeah?

262
00:19:12.067 --> 00:19:14.183
Do you like...

263
00:19:15.100 --> 00:19:17.185
that woman?

264
00:19:18.367 --> 00:19:20.256
Well...

265
00:19:22.091 --> 00:19:23.926
Yes.

266
00:19:25.029 --> 00:19:27.596
She's my girlfriend.

267
00:19:33.537 --> 00:19:36.805
What do you think?

268
00:19:38.420 --> 00:19:40.945
Can I be honest?

269
00:19:40.945 --> 00:19:43.211
Clear.

270
00:19:43.211 --> 00:19:45.447
She seems a little crazy.

271
00:19:50.153 --> 00:19:52.922
Sol's boyfriend is you, not that guy.

272
00:19:52.922 --> 00:19:56.240
Why did you leave like a loser
instead of entering with confidence?

273
00:19:56.240 --> 00:19:58.994
The pork chop

274
00:20:01.068 --> 00:20:04.220
It was crap next to the steak.

275
00:20:04.220 --> 00:20:05.167
That?

276
00:20:05.167 --> 00:20:07.036
Steak is steak.

277
00:20:07.036 --> 00:20:09.673
Pork chop is pork chop.
What a fool.

278
00:20:09.673 --> 00:20:12.541
What's wrong with food
of Delicious Battered Pork?

279
00:20:13.453 --> 00:20:17.112
I want to believe that it is an eternal love.

280
00:20:18.167 --> 00:20:21.383
Will I be in Sol's future?

281
00:20:29.334 --> 00:20:31.994
Generally,

282
00:20:33.267 --> 00:20:36.665
You see Scorpio out there at this time,

283
00:20:38.034 --> 00:20:39.603
but it's not there.

284
00:20:39.603 --> 00:20:40.837
Like me.

285
00:20:40.837 --> 00:20:45.540
Yes, a weak presence just like yours.

286
00:20:46.534 --> 00:20:48.344
Curse.

287
00:20:49.912 --> 00:20:53.787
Horoscope for Scorpio.

288
00:20:53.787 --> 00:20:56.147
Who pays attention to the horoscope today?

289
00:20:56.147 --> 00:20:58.154
"You will be confused.

290
00:20:58.154 --> 00:21:01.529
Many people's emotions will be entangled.

291
00:21:01.529 --> 00:21:06.095
You will suffer from an unwanted love triangle,

292
00:21:06.095 --> 00:21:09.598
So get ready."

293
00:21:10.709 --> 00:21:14.369
Yes, get ready, Scorpio.

294
00:21:17.340 --> 00:21:20.075
Wait, aren't you a Scorpio too?

295
00:21:27.483 --> 00:21:30.005
[Guide]

296
00:21:39.345 --> 00:21:40.585
Hello?

297
00:21:40.585 --> 00:21:42.571
Are you alive?

298
00:21:42.571 --> 00:21:43.733
Sorry?

299
00:21:43.733 --> 00:21:45.906
Why don't you answer if you didn't die?

300
00:21:45.906 --> 00:21:48.236
Don't you want to see me anymore?

301
00:21:49.238 --> 00:21:51.876
It's not that, at all.

302
00:21:51.876 --> 00:21:54.245
So, are you playing hard to get?

303
00:21:54.245 --> 00:21:56.045
Of course not.

304
00:21:56.045 --> 00:21:58.048
I was about to call you...

305
00:21:58.048 --> 00:21:59.265
Liar.

306
00:21:59.265 --> 00:22:00.718
It isn't true.

307
00:22:00.718 --> 00:22:04.152
I was about to call you
to see each other tomorrow...

308
00:22:06.490 --> 00:22:08.826
Were you talking on the phone?

309
00:22:08.826 --> 00:22:10.413
Talking on the phone?

310
00:22:10.413 --> 00:22:13.362
No. What phone?

311
00:22:15.264 --> 00:22:17.000
That?

312
00:22:17.000 --> 00:22:18.801
What's wrong with him?

313
00:22:18.801 --> 00:22:22.304
I'm sure I heard you talking.

314
00:22:22.304 --> 00:22:23.641
Dad, what about dinner?

315
00:22:23.641 --> 00:22:25.409
I'm going to eat. And you?

316
00:22:25.409 --> 00:22:26.968
I bought pork chops.

317
00:22:26.968 --> 00:22:29.079
Pork chops.

318
00:22:29.079 --> 00:22:31.146
What a good idea.

319
00:22:32.348 --> 00:22:35.284
- Let's eat together, hurry up.
- OK.

320
00:22:37.400 --> 00:22:40.188
- Dad, by chance...
- What? What's happening?

321
00:22:43.201 --> 00:22:46.661
Are you talking to mom's photo?

322
00:22:47.787 --> 00:22:49.490
That?

323
00:22:56.539 --> 00:22:58.573
Well...

324
00:22:58.573 --> 00:23:01.276
Sure, sometimes yes.

325
00:23:03.586 --> 00:23:04.947
Take your time to get out.

326
00:23:04.947 --> 00:23:06.634
Alright.

327
00:23:06.634 --> 00:23:08.450
Yes.

328
00:23:25.701 --> 00:23:27.736
Everything ready.

329
00:23:36.881 --> 00:23:38.648
Look who's here.

330
00:23:39.482 --> 00:23:42.150
Why are you looking at me like that?

331
00:23:42.150 --> 00:23:43.762
Dad, have you had dinner yet?

332
00:23:43.762 --> 00:23:46.221
I'm setting the table.

333
00:23:59.324 --> 00:24:02.084
Don't know our password?

334
00:24:02.084 --> 00:24:05.707
Your mom wanted it to be your birthday.

335
00:24:09.918 --> 00:24:11.414
Let's change it to the date of mine.

336
00:24:11.414 --> 00:24:14.549
Why is it birthday
from someone who doesn't live here?

337
00:24:14.549 --> 00:24:16.918
Change it to the date of yours.

338
00:24:17.987 --> 00:24:20.689
Lately, you come very often.

339
00:24:21.825 --> 00:24:23.859
And?

340
00:24:27.392 --> 00:24:30.632
I'm glad we eat together more often.

341
00:24:31.701 --> 00:24:34.202
You should have come when mom was there.

342
00:24:37.673 --> 00:24:42.701
Let me see, this is your first time cooking.

343
00:24:42.701 --> 00:24:44.479
No?

344
00:24:54.290 --> 00:24:55.526
How are you doing?

345
00:24:55.526 --> 00:24:57.492
Is it good?

346
00:24:58.961 --> 00:25:01.036
It has to be good.

347
00:25:01.036 --> 00:25:02.765
It's your first dish.

348
00:25:02.765 --> 00:25:06.201
Oh really? What a relief.

349
00:25:10.740 --> 00:25:11.936
Yes...

350
00:25:11.936 --> 00:25:14.267
It's your first time,

351
00:25:14.267 --> 00:25:16.912
that's why it tastes like that.

352
00:25:17.615 --> 00:25:22.050
What did you get into cooking if you never do it?

353
00:25:22.920 --> 00:25:26.254
How much curry did you do to bring so much?

354
00:25:26.857 --> 00:25:27.836
Yes, that.

355
00:25:27.836 --> 00:25:31.445
Who were you planning to eat this with?
Why did you do so much?

356
00:25:31.445 --> 00:25:33.663
You're supposed to do a lot of curry.

357
00:25:33.663 --> 00:25:39.567
It gets richer as the days go by.

358
00:25:39.567 --> 00:25:41.536
That's how it is.

359
00:25:42.145 --> 00:25:45.540
It will taste even better tomorrow, right?

360
00:25:46.644 --> 00:25:48.336
That?

361
00:25:55.484 --> 00:25:56.885
- Yes...
- What?

362
00:25:56.885 --> 00:25:59.930
It's delicious now,
but tomorrow it will be even better.

363
00:25:59.930 --> 00:26:01.190
Isn't it?

364
00:26:01.190 --> 00:26:03.527
- Give me more.
- Why not?

365
00:26:03.527 --> 00:26:07.796
Who told you that?

366
00:26:08.550 --> 00:26:10.265
That?

367
00:26:11.902 --> 00:26:13.701
- Dad.
- Yeah?

368
00:26:13.701 --> 00:26:15.871
Are you seeing...?

369
00:26:16.470 --> 00:26:18.548
- That?
- That?

370
00:26:18.548 --> 00:26:20.044
That?

371
00:26:20.044 --> 00:26:21.810
Yeah?

372
00:26:25.015 --> 00:26:26.371
- That?
- That?

373
00:26:26.371 --> 00:26:28.150
No.

374
00:26:28.968 --> 00:26:32.354
I'm dating someone.

375
00:26:33.722 --> 00:26:38.059
I know it's a bit inappropriate.

376
00:26:47.701 --> 00:26:50.138
Is that okay with you?

377
00:26:51.342 --> 00:26:53.509
Of course.

378
00:26:53.509 --> 00:26:56.133
love someone

379
00:26:56.133 --> 00:26:58.713
It's a blessing.

380
00:27:00.149 --> 00:27:02.223
Congratulations.

381
00:27:03.385 --> 00:27:06.299
Did you give yourself away so easily?

382
00:27:06.299 --> 00:27:08.691
I should have kept my letters longer.

383
00:27:08.691 --> 00:27:11.259
Too bad.

384
00:27:15.499 --> 00:27:17.599
What a waste.

385
00:27:39.053 --> 00:27:41.289
Still haven't finished saving everything?

386
00:27:41.859 --> 00:27:43.694
I'm done.

387
00:27:43.694 --> 00:27:47.162
Me too.

388
00:27:51.133 --> 00:27:53.735
It's a little empty.

389
00:27:55.642 --> 00:27:58.406
You can put photos of your idols
or whatever you like.

390
00:27:59.276 --> 00:28:01.543
Tell me if you need anything.

391
00:28:02.911 --> 00:28:04.553
I'm fine.

392
00:28:04.553 --> 00:28:06.881
What kind of son are you?

393
00:28:07.983 --> 00:28:11.386
You should insist that I buy you things.

394
00:28:15.960 --> 00:28:17.759
Insist?

395
00:28:22.744 --> 00:28:23.933
That is,

396
00:28:23.933 --> 00:28:26.234
You should ask me to spoil you.

397
00:28:30.574 --> 00:28:33.007
That you pamper me?

398
00:28:37.133 --> 00:28:39.581
I mean, come closer.

399
00:28:52.901 --> 00:28:55.296
Finish with your room.

400
00:28:57.995 --> 00:28:59.801
Daniel.

401
00:29:02.534 --> 00:29:05.974
Can I invite...

402
00:29:07.567 --> 00:29:10.445
take my girlfriend home?

403
00:29:16.527 --> 00:29:19.754
I would like...

404
00:29:20.334 --> 00:29:24.526
that they know each other.

405
00:29:32.634 --> 00:29:34.069
OK.

406
00:29:34.681 --> 00:29:36.337
Oh really?

407
00:29:37.001 --> 00:29:39.140
If you are happy,

408
00:29:39.534 --> 00:29:41.676
I am too.

409
00:30:17.646 --> 00:30:19.748
The dye...

410
00:30:20.315 --> 00:30:23.485
I left it half dyed.

411
00:30:23.485 --> 00:30:25.456
Just like that.

412
00:30:25.456 --> 00:30:27.589
It looks strange, doesn't it?

413
00:30:30.993 --> 00:30:32.461
Give me your phone, please.

414
00:30:32.461 --> 00:30:33.878
That?

415
00:30:33.878 --> 00:30:36.598
Because?

416
00:30:47.509 --> 00:30:50.112
It can't be, I knew it.

417
00:30:50.112 --> 00:30:52.998
Did you schedule me as a "Guide"?

418
00:30:52.998 --> 00:30:55.416
Did you know I have a name?

419
00:30:58.654 --> 00:31:00.508
[Ja Yeong]

420
00:31:05.394 --> 00:31:07.996
And how did you save my number?

421
00:31:12.835 --> 00:31:16.004
[Jin Ho]

422
00:31:24.513 --> 00:31:26.681
Tell me now.

423
00:31:28.085 --> 00:31:29.342
Tell you what?

424
00:31:29.342 --> 00:31:31.001
The excuse men make

425
00:31:31.001 --> 00:31:34.856
when they don't call for days
after spending the night with a woman.

426
00:31:38.492 --> 00:31:40.295
The truth...

427
00:31:41.501 --> 00:31:43.731
I was afraid.

428
00:31:45.334 --> 00:31:47.302
About what?

429
00:31:48.532 --> 00:31:51.067
That someone would discover

430
00:31:51.067 --> 00:31:53.775
that I feel something for you.

431
00:31:58.547 --> 00:31:59.332
And then?

432
00:31:59.332 --> 00:32:01.182
But thanks to you,

433
00:32:01.867 --> 00:32:04.622
I gathered courage.

434
00:32:04.622 --> 00:32:06.522
I made a decision.

435
00:32:06.522 --> 00:32:08.957
I live my life, no one else.

436
00:32:08.957 --> 00:32:12.668
I have to find my happiness.

437
00:32:12.668 --> 00:32:14.354
Or not?

438
00:32:17.166 --> 00:32:21.369
From now on,
I won't care what other people think anymore.

439
00:32:23.439 --> 00:32:25.206
Boss?

440
00:32:25.864 --> 00:32:27.376
- Yes.
- It's good to see you.

441
00:32:27.376 --> 00:32:28.412
Yes, I'm glad to see you too.

442
00:32:28.412 --> 00:32:30.447
What brings you here?

443
00:32:30.447 --> 00:32:32.447
Well...

444
00:32:33.370 --> 00:32:35.610
The weather is nice, so I came for a walk.

445
00:32:35.610 --> 00:32:37.571
Is he with you?

446
00:32:37.571 --> 00:32:40.688
No, I don't know her.

447
00:32:41.456 --> 00:32:42.257
What brings you here?

448
00:32:42.257 --> 00:32:44.851
A customer service program event.

449
00:32:44.851 --> 00:32:46.350
They are all there.

450
00:32:46.350 --> 00:32:48.457
- The customer service program.
- Yes.

451
00:32:48.457 --> 00:32:49.598
Why don't you come?

452
00:32:49.598 --> 00:32:52.033
- Seem to you?
- Yes.

453
00:32:56.505 --> 00:32:58.340
The boss is here.

454
00:32:58.340 --> 00:33:00.033
- Hello.
- Hello.

455
00:33:00.033 --> 00:33:02.277
So long.

456
00:33:14.001 --> 00:33:16.324
And this?

457
00:33:17.233 --> 00:33:19.962
A friend is traveling
and she asked me to take care of her,

458
00:33:19.962 --> 00:33:21.801
so I brought it this morning.

459
00:33:21.801 --> 00:33:23.765
What friend?

460
00:33:24.534 --> 00:33:26.067
Well... the one over there...

461
00:33:26.067 --> 00:33:27.503
One from Bundang.

462
00:33:27.503 --> 00:33:28.837
The one from Dongtan.

463
00:33:28.837 --> 00:33:30.424
Don't you know him?

464
00:33:30.424 --> 00:33:32.306
I think you know him.

465
00:33:33.408 --> 00:33:34.804
I don't know him.

466
00:33:34.804 --> 00:33:37.646
You're very good-looking.

467
00:33:37.646 --> 00:33:40.114
It's a girl.

468
00:33:40.816 --> 00:33:41.844
I'm sorry.

469
00:33:41.844 --> 00:33:43.918
You are very cute.

470
00:33:44.886 --> 00:33:48.224
Reminds me of when you two were kids.

471
00:33:48.224 --> 00:33:51.267
The meal time had to be respected,
clean them, play...

472
00:33:51.267 --> 00:33:54.968
The truth is, it was the best time of my life.

473
00:33:54.968 --> 00:33:55.964
tell me,

474
00:33:55.964 --> 00:33:58.667
What's the guy Jun Kyung is dating like?

475
00:33:58.667 --> 00:34:00.468
Do you know him?

476
00:34:01.141 --> 00:34:03.234
I saw him once.

477
00:34:03.234 --> 00:34:05.373
I don't know if I can say I know him.

478
00:34:05.881 --> 00:34:07.808
Well...

479
00:34:07.808 --> 00:34:10.141
I think he is a good person.

480
00:34:10.141 --> 00:34:11.949
Yeah? What does that mean?

481
00:34:11.949 --> 00:34:14.634
Only someone like him would date her.

482
00:34:14.634 --> 00:34:16.490
Clear.

483
00:34:17.853 --> 00:34:19.667
What's it called?

484
00:34:19.667 --> 00:34:21.200
Boom.

485
00:34:21.200 --> 00:34:22.493
- Boom.
- Boom.

486
00:34:22.493 --> 00:34:24.291
Boom.

487
00:34:36.106 --> 00:34:38.444
Nice to meet you.

488
00:34:38.444 --> 00:34:40.875
I'm Ju Do Hyun.

489
00:34:47.616 --> 00:34:50.385
Thank you for suggesting the visit.

490
00:34:52.089 --> 00:34:55.156
How not to do it.

491
00:34:59.376 --> 00:35:01.863
I wanted to pay my respects.

492
00:35:09.073 --> 00:35:11.305
What a surprise.

493
00:35:12.477 --> 00:35:15.510
This is where loved ones are buried.

494
00:35:16.277 --> 00:35:18.613
Why is no one sad?

495
00:35:19.434 --> 00:35:21.616
Everyone smiles.

496
00:35:25.249 --> 00:35:28.189
Because those times are behind us.

497
00:35:28.824 --> 00:35:30.767
Now...

498
00:35:30.767 --> 00:35:33.127
they miss them...

499
00:35:33.868 --> 00:35:36.030
and they want to see them.

500
00:35:38.917 --> 00:35:41.602
They are probably happy
to come see them.

501
00:35:49.010 --> 00:35:51.979
Did they make it so pretty
so that they visit them more?

502
00:36:02.591 --> 00:36:04.059
I'm fine.

503
00:36:04.059 --> 00:36:06.360
It's dad I'm worried about.

504
00:36:13.671 --> 00:36:14.772
Above!

505
00:36:14.772 --> 00:36:16.537
Above!

506
00:36:17.207 --> 00:36:18.843
What are you going to do?

507
00:36:18.843 --> 00:36:20.775
Above!

508
00:36:23.242 --> 00:36:25.049
It's mommy.

509
00:36:25.049 --> 00:36:27.084
It's mommy.

510
00:36:27.084 --> 00:36:29.550
Look, it's mommy.

511
00:36:31.553 --> 00:36:33.181
What time is it over there?

512
00:36:33.181 --> 00:36:35.924
<i>There is only one hour difference in Hong Kong.</i>

513
00:36:35.924 --> 00:36:37.426
Just one hour?

514
00:36:37.426 --> 00:36:39.561
I had no idea, I was never abroad.

515
00:36:39.561 --> 00:36:40.962
<i>Is our Bom okay?</i>

516
00:36:40.962 --> 00:36:42.942
Yes, I was playing with her.

517
00:36:42.942 --> 00:36:46.133
Jump very tenderly.

518
00:36:46.968 --> 00:36:48.821
<i>I miss you, Bom.</i>

519
00:36:48.821 --> 00:36:49.871
<i>See you the day after tomorrow.</i>

520
00:36:49.871 --> 00:36:52.808
I miss you too.

521
00:36:52.808 --> 00:36:55.576
<i>I miss you too, Jin Ho.</i>

522
00:37:00.982 --> 00:37:04.034
I was very afraid

523
00:37:04.034 --> 00:37:06.822
that this treatment was painful,

524
00:37:06.822 --> 00:37:08.772
but it doesn't hurt anything.

525
00:37:08.772 --> 00:37:10.411
I told you.

526
00:37:10.411 --> 00:37:12.394
Jun Kyung, why don't you do it too?

527
00:37:12.394 --> 00:37:13.228
OK.

528
00:37:13.228 --> 00:37:14.912
Do you have a husband?

529
00:37:14.912 --> 00:37:17.165
Do you have children? Do you have a mother-in-law?

530
00:37:17.165 --> 00:37:19.968
No, it does not have a source of stress
that causes stains.

531
00:37:19.968 --> 00:37:21.951
But you will be getting ahead of the treatment.

532
00:37:21.951 --> 00:37:25.009
It's great to play with things like that, right?

533
00:37:25.009 --> 00:37:25.976
Of course.

534
00:37:25.976 --> 00:37:27.801
At that age he is busy with academia.

535
00:37:27.801 --> 00:37:30.178
Damn, what could it be?

536
00:37:30.178 --> 00:37:34.281
You have children in high school,
you must have some idea.

537
00:37:34.281 --> 00:37:36.151
You are totally dedicated.

538
00:37:36.151 --> 00:37:37.939
I won't go to an inauguration with nothing.

539
00:37:37.939 --> 00:37:39.321
Do what you always do.

540
00:37:39.321 --> 00:37:40.756
For you, money is the best.

541
00:37:40.756 --> 00:37:43.191
He hates wasting emotions and time.

542
00:37:43.191 --> 00:37:45.319
Always solve everything with money.

543
00:37:45.319 --> 00:37:47.562
How am I going to give money to a child?

544
00:37:47.562 --> 00:37:48.697
Come on,

545
00:37:48.697 --> 00:37:52.267
you gave money to my daughters
for his fourth birthday.

546
00:37:52.267 --> 00:37:53.929
Now you act motherly.

547
00:37:53.929 --> 00:37:56.449
Do you really want to look so good with him?

548
00:37:56.449 --> 00:37:58.507
The good image has already disappeared,

549
00:37:58.507 --> 00:38:01.343
But I don't want to make it worse.

550
00:38:01.343 --> 00:38:02.344
How about this?

551
00:38:02.344 --> 00:38:04.378
Do you think he will like it?

552
00:38:04.946 --> 00:38:09.717
Do you dare to guess
the style of a high school student?

553
00:38:10.254 --> 00:38:11.052
Yes.

554
00:38:11.052 --> 00:38:13.448
Look, how about this?

555
00:38:13.448 --> 00:38:15.157
Everyone studies with that.

556
00:38:15.157 --> 00:38:18.160
Every kid has one of those nowadays.

557
00:38:18.160 --> 00:38:20.628
Since when?

558
00:38:20.628 --> 00:38:22.100
Ready.

559
00:38:22.100 --> 00:38:23.265
- That's it?
- Yes.

560
00:38:23.265 --> 00:38:25.133
Pass me the mirror.

561
00:38:25.133 --> 00:38:26.867
The mirror.

562
00:38:29.968 --> 00:38:32.076
Heavens.

563
00:38:32.076 --> 00:38:35.242
Look how my face lit up.

564
00:38:37.434 --> 00:38:39.213
Go.

565
00:38:41.085 --> 00:38:43.598
- Is it Mr. Ju Do Hyun?
- Yes.

566
00:38:43.598 --> 00:38:44.452
Wait a moment.

567
00:38:44.452 --> 00:38:47.367
- Can you sign me here, please?
- OK.

568
00:38:56.266 --> 00:38:58.133
How did you come up with a gift like that?

569
00:38:58.133 --> 00:39:00.267
Alright?

570
00:39:00.267 --> 00:39:01.636
I hesitated a little.

571
00:39:01.636 --> 00:39:02.871
Do you think Daniel will like it?

572
00:39:02.871 --> 00:39:05.032
Of course you will like it.

573
00:39:05.032 --> 00:39:07.108
I would never expect a gift like that.

574
00:39:07.108 --> 00:39:08.443
By the way,

575
00:39:08.443 --> 00:39:11.533
what are you going to put here?

576
00:39:11.533 --> 00:39:14.649
You'll see, you won't believe it.

577
00:39:24.233 --> 00:39:27.028
It's much better out here.

578
00:39:30.034 --> 00:39:32.700
They look happy.

579
00:39:48.485 --> 00:39:49.467
Yes.

580
00:39:49.467 --> 00:39:51.286
Hello. Can I come in?

581
00:39:51.286 --> 00:39:53.721
Yes, it happens.

582
00:39:55.068 --> 00:39:57.158
Okay, understood.

583
00:39:58.334 --> 00:39:59.827
Yes.

584
00:40:00.467 --> 00:40:01.200
I'm leaving, excuse me.

585
00:40:01.200 --> 00:40:03.298
You didn't have to bring anything.

586
00:40:03.298 --> 00:40:05.099
OK.

587
00:40:08.667 --> 00:40:10.204
Take a seat.

588
00:40:17.567 --> 00:40:19.914
Why do you think I called you?

589
00:40:21.870 --> 00:40:23.851
I'm not sure.

590
00:40:24.989 --> 00:40:26.630
Do you want to drink something?

591
00:40:26.630 --> 00:40:28.321
Sorry?

592
00:40:31.459 --> 00:40:33.428
I wish she would put in that much effort in her tasks.

593
00:40:33.428 --> 00:40:35.530
She's only good at bringing things like this.

594
00:40:35.530 --> 00:40:38.800
Should I consider it an effort too?

595
00:40:41.567 --> 00:40:44.030
Let me see.

596
00:40:50.665 --> 00:40:53.581
You turned in your homework again, right?

597
00:40:53.581 --> 00:40:55.087
Yes.

598
00:40:55.087 --> 00:40:57.652
Why did you do it?

599
00:40:58.586 --> 00:41:01.207
Did you get angry because I scolded you?

600
00:41:01.207 --> 00:41:02.587
No, it's not that.

601
00:41:02.587 --> 00:41:04.747
If not, there is no reason to resubmit it,

602
00:41:04.747 --> 00:41:06.807
because the deadline passed
and the notes are set.

603
00:41:06.807 --> 00:41:09.130
It is useless to do so.

604
00:41:11.200 --> 00:41:12.667
Well...

605
00:41:13.167 --> 00:41:14.502
I...

606
00:41:14.502 --> 00:41:17.905
I wanted to try to make a proper effort.

607
00:41:20.334 --> 00:41:22.076
Effort?

608
00:41:24.562 --> 00:41:26.448
If I remember correctly,

609
00:41:26.448 --> 00:41:28.817
You are in the Astronomy Department.

610
00:41:28.817 --> 00:41:30.423
Yes.

611
00:41:31.119 --> 00:41:33.287
Is that why?

612
00:41:33.287 --> 00:41:35.256
You are very sentimental.

613
00:41:37.101 --> 00:41:38.859
Thank you.

614
00:41:39.622 --> 00:41:41.662
Do you want to try an internship?

615
00:41:42.132 --> 00:41:43.565
Yes.

616
00:41:43.565 --> 00:41:46.468
A colleague at JCBC

617
00:41:46.468 --> 00:41:49.804
He said they are looking for someone
to carry out journalistic investigations.

618
00:41:49.804 --> 00:41:53.008
Hyo Jung came earlier
curious about that too.

619
00:41:53.008 --> 00:41:54.812
As much as I try to be fair,

620
00:41:54.812 --> 00:41:59.173
Justice has a limit, right?

621
00:42:00.684 --> 00:42:05.352
I value your attitude much more.

622
00:42:12.611 --> 00:42:14.995
So will you do it or not?

623
00:42:17.401 --> 00:42:18.934
Is the water temperature okay?

624
00:42:18.934 --> 00:42:22.169
Alright? Of course!

625
00:42:22.938 --> 00:42:25.172
You are pretty, very pretty.

626
00:42:30.512 --> 00:42:31.980
- Hello?
<i>- Dad.</i>

627
00:42:31.980 --> 00:42:34.711
I will be a research intern at the station.

628
00:42:34.711 --> 00:42:36.292
- Research intern?
<i>- Yes.</i>

629
00:42:36.292 --> 00:42:38.092
It sounds very important.

630
00:42:38.092 --> 00:42:41.271
My teacher recommended me
compared to those who have master's degrees and doctorates.

631
00:42:41.271 --> 00:42:43.491
That's my son. I'm very proud of you.

632
00:42:43.491 --> 00:42:45.460
Congratulations.

633
00:42:45.460 --> 00:42:46.512
Today I will be late.

634
00:42:46.512 --> 00:42:48.129
<i>Okay, have a drink with your friends.</i>

635
00:42:48.129 --> 00:42:50.032
I also have things to do,
so don't worry.

636
00:42:50.032 --> 00:42:51.599
Maybe I won't go home today.

637
00:42:51.599 --> 00:42:52.901
Won't you come home?

638
00:42:52.901 --> 00:42:55.503
Well, enjoy your drinks
and don't come if you don't want to.

639
00:42:55.503 --> 00:42:57.972
- OK.
<i>- Dad.</i>

640
00:42:58.509 --> 00:43:00.341
I love you.

641
00:43:08.292 --> 00:43:09.644
Where did he go?

642
00:43:09.644 --> 00:43:11.267
There you are.

643
00:43:11.267 --> 00:43:13.667
Come on.

644
00:43:15.901 --> 00:43:17.968
Let's finish with the bathroom.

645
00:43:17.968 --> 00:43:19.627
You are pretty.

646
00:43:19.627 --> 00:43:21.528
Oh really?

647
00:43:28.136 --> 00:43:29.953
It's incredible.

648
00:43:29.953 --> 00:43:32.833
I owe you one, so I'll invite you.

649
00:43:32.833 --> 00:43:34.173
<i>What did I tell you?</i>

650
00:43:34.173 --> 00:43:36.111
I told you you weren't pathetic.

651
00:43:36.111 --> 00:43:38.979
I said you were great, right?

652
00:43:38.979 --> 00:43:40.682
It's a fact.

653
00:43:40.682 --> 00:43:41.669
OK.

654
00:43:41.669 --> 00:43:45.256
I'll treat you to pork chops,
<i>jjolmyeon</i>, <i>sushi</i> and <i>tteokbokki</i>.

655
00:43:45.256 --> 00:43:47.221
Thank you.

656
00:43:52.627 --> 00:43:56.530
I'm officially a working adult!

657
00:43:59.260 --> 00:44:05.030
<i></i>

658
00:44:10.745 --> 00:44:12.346
Hello.

659
00:44:15.719 --> 00:44:17.618
You arrived.

660
00:44:24.092 --> 00:44:26.093
Crescent Betta.

661
00:44:28.796 --> 00:44:30.999
It looks very mysterious.

662
00:44:30.999 --> 00:44:33.001
But he looks very alone,

663
00:44:33.001 --> 00:44:35.837
Shall we bring him one more to be his friend?

664
00:44:35.837 --> 00:44:38.200
It is difficult for this species
live with other fish.

665
00:44:38.200 --> 00:44:39.927
They say they usually live alone.

666
00:44:39.927 --> 00:44:41.635
Well...

667
00:44:42.200 --> 00:44:44.117
So...

668
00:44:44.834 --> 00:44:47.915
Daniel can be your friend.

669
00:44:51.786 --> 00:44:53.901
Once he adapts to the fish tank,

670
00:44:53.901 --> 00:44:56.361
It rises to the surface asking for food.

671
00:44:56.361 --> 00:44:59.793
He is affectionate like a puppy,
That's why they call it "aquatic dog."

672
00:45:02.564 --> 00:45:04.598
Isn't it nice?

673
00:45:07.502 --> 00:45:10.370
I told you, he's shy around people he doesn't know.

674
00:45:12.142 --> 00:45:15.676
Don't be shy, it's just a fish.

675
00:45:16.613 --> 00:45:18.465
Here we are!

676
00:45:21.516 --> 00:45:22.634
Ja Yeong,

677
00:45:22.634 --> 00:45:25.519
It's time to wake up from oblivion.

678
00:45:27.422 --> 00:45:30.424
The reality when you wake up is much better, right?

679
00:45:31.392 --> 00:45:33.494
Boom, have you been okay?

680
00:45:33.494 --> 00:45:35.630
Did you play a lot?

681
00:45:35.630 --> 00:45:36.674
How did you spend it?

682
00:45:36.674 --> 00:45:38.314
I had a very bad time

683
00:45:38.314 --> 00:45:40.094
because I was craving kimchi jjigae.

684
00:45:40.094 --> 00:45:41.172
That?

685
00:45:41.172 --> 00:45:42.970
<i>Kimchi jjigae</i>?

686
00:45:43.638 --> 00:45:47.074
I know a place
which makes a delicious <i>kimchi jjigae</i>.

687
00:45:48.109 --> 00:45:49.877
Come on.

688
00:45:51.329 --> 00:45:53.480
Happens.

689
00:46:00.989 --> 00:46:03.093
It's very nice.

690
00:46:03.093 --> 00:46:05.429
It's nothing special.

691
00:46:05.429 --> 00:46:07.895
My son will be home late today,

692
00:46:08.369 --> 00:46:10.397
He said he might not come home.

693
00:46:11.437 --> 00:46:13.871
I will welcome you
with a delicious <i>kimchi jjigae</i>.

694
00:46:13.871 --> 00:46:16.407
I brought you a gift.

695
00:46:16.407 --> 00:46:17.537
A gift?

696
00:46:17.537 --> 00:46:18.909
Same t-shirts.

697
00:46:18.909 --> 00:46:20.874
Same t-shirts?

698
00:46:22.477 --> 00:46:24.100
But...

699
00:46:24.100 --> 00:46:25.878
Is it okay for me to come in?

700
00:46:25.878 --> 00:46:27.814
Alright.

701
00:46:29.350 --> 00:46:30.718
Ja Yeong,

702
00:46:30.718 --> 00:46:33.487
wait here a moment, please.

703
00:47:22.383 --> 00:47:24.371
[Eternal Love]

704
00:47:30.714 --> 00:47:33.184
Haven't finished the test yet?

705
00:47:33.184 --> 00:47:35.382
Why is it taking so long?

706
00:47:45.587 --> 00:47:46.501
Hello, aunt.

707
00:47:46.501 --> 00:47:47.528
Hello.

708
00:47:47.528 --> 00:47:50.998
I'm in your neighborhood, I brought radish kimchi.

709
00:47:50.998 --> 00:47:52.900
Your dad loves it.

710
00:47:52.900 --> 00:47:55.901
I'll stop by after running an errand.
He's at home, right?

711
00:47:55.901 --> 00:47:58.305
He doesn't answer the phone.

712
00:47:58.906 --> 00:48:00.681
I'm not at home right now,

713
00:48:00.681 --> 00:48:02.813
and dad said he would go out.

714
00:48:02.813 --> 00:48:04.221
Oh really?

715
00:48:04.221 --> 00:48:08.014
So what do I do with this?

716
00:48:19.563 --> 00:48:22.029
What do you like to do, Daniel?

717
00:48:22.599 --> 00:48:24.531
Do you have any hobbies?

718
00:48:27.902 --> 00:48:29.689
Why do you ask me?

719
00:48:33.310 --> 00:48:35.375
I'm curious.

720
00:48:36.447 --> 00:48:38.378
I don't have any.

721
00:48:41.246 --> 00:48:43.918
You like to ride a skateboard.

722
00:48:43.918 --> 00:48:46.973
You always watch videos and practice tricks.

723
00:48:46.973 --> 00:48:50.334
He also likes music, like me,

724
00:48:50.334 --> 00:48:51.853
but we have different tastes.

725
00:48:51.853 --> 00:48:53.827
He only likes hiphop.

726
00:49:02.036 --> 00:49:04.213
Can I serve you a little? It's delicious.

727
00:49:04.213 --> 00:49:05.574
I'm not well.

728
00:49:05.574 --> 00:49:07.575
I feel bad
for being the only one who eats something so delicious.

729
00:49:07.575 --> 00:49:09.636
No.

730
00:49:12.483 --> 00:49:14.381
Are you okay?

731
00:49:15.734 --> 00:49:18.919
- Are you OK?
- I'm fine.

732
00:49:19.660 --> 00:49:22.222
I'm sorry, dad.

733
00:49:29.230 --> 00:49:32.065
Don't worry, it was an accident.

734
00:49:41.909 --> 00:49:43.710
Yes.

735
00:49:51.868 --> 00:49:54.388
I'm very sorry.

736
00:49:54.388 --> 00:49:56.356
Because?

737
00:49:56.356 --> 00:50:00.661
I think I created an awkward situation.

738
00:50:01.198 --> 00:50:03.529
If anyone was uncomfortable, it was Daniel, not me.

739
00:50:03.529 --> 00:50:05.365
I'm fine.

740
00:50:08.205 --> 00:50:10.904
You have nothing to worry about.

741
00:50:17.000 --> 00:50:18.679
What's happening?

742
00:50:21.100 --> 00:50:23.416
I'll walk you down.

743
00:50:23.416 --> 00:50:26.260
Right, your shirt.

744
00:50:33.133 --> 00:50:35.062
Daniel...

745
00:50:35.599 --> 00:50:37.764
until next time.

746
00:50:44.405 --> 00:50:46.173
<i>Hure</i>.

747
00:50:46.974 --> 00:50:48.312
That?

748
00:50:48.312 --> 00:50:50.544
What does it mean?

749
00:50:54.717 --> 00:50:57.117
It doesn't mean anything.

750
00:51:00.501 --> 00:51:02.723
Come on.

751
00:51:10.364 --> 00:51:12.066
I told you I would accompany you.

752
00:51:12.066 --> 00:51:14.558
Who asks for a car
and then walk someone home?

753
00:51:14.558 --> 00:51:16.670
I'm fine.

754
00:51:18.439 --> 00:51:20.367
A while ago...

755
00:51:20.367 --> 00:51:23.276
What were you talking about with Daniel?

756
00:51:26.847 --> 00:51:28.915
It's a secret.

757
00:51:32.049 --> 00:51:34.225
You probably don't know.

758
00:51:34.225 --> 00:51:36.189
That?

759
00:51:38.503 --> 00:51:42.762
I was dying of nerves.

760
00:51:45.366 --> 00:51:49.870
I just became a father out of nowhere.

761
00:51:50.731 --> 00:51:53.640
Now suddenly I introduce you to my girlfriend

762
00:51:54.334 --> 00:51:58.478
a son I barely know.

763
00:52:01.806 --> 00:52:04.400
Thank you very much

764
00:52:04.400 --> 00:52:07.487
for making the effort.

765
00:52:10.858 --> 00:52:14.161
- Arrive.
- The car arrived.

766
00:52:42.363 --> 00:52:44.183
It looks delicious.

767
00:52:44.183 --> 00:52:46.726
Thanks for the food.

768
00:52:50.201 --> 00:52:52.002
How is it?

769
00:52:52.002 --> 00:52:53.620
It looks like a restaurant.

770
00:52:53.620 --> 00:52:57.504
- It's delicious.
- What a relief.

771
00:52:59.476 --> 00:53:00.501
Ja Yeong,

772
00:53:00.501 --> 00:53:02.642
Also try the omelette.

773
00:53:08.516 --> 00:53:09.950
It's very tasty!

774
00:53:09.950 --> 00:53:12.819
How do you cook so well?

775
00:53:21.796 --> 00:53:25.765
Why are you looking at me like that? You make me blush.

776
00:53:26.217 --> 00:53:28.035
Because you're pretty.

777
00:53:28.035 --> 00:53:31.638
You look very pretty eating what I prepared.

778
00:53:43.721 --> 00:53:46.286
It's okay, sir.

779
00:53:48.824 --> 00:53:50.920
Clear.

780
00:53:50.920 --> 00:53:52.429
Yes.

781
00:53:52.429 --> 00:53:55.028
Have a good day.

782
00:53:56.800 --> 00:53:59.069
They will take care

783
00:53:59.069 --> 00:54:01.534
of payment for the sports center
next week.

784
00:54:06.006 --> 00:54:09.946
That's why you don't have to send the goods yet.

785
00:54:09.946 --> 00:54:11.946
The people

786
00:54:11.946 --> 00:54:15.015
They should have confidence.

787
00:54:18.601 --> 00:54:22.322
They will pay later.

788
00:54:23.190 --> 00:54:25.701
Are you sure they won't scam us?

789
00:54:25.701 --> 00:54:29.996
Who would scam us for that? They will pay.

790
00:54:32.102 --> 00:54:34.034
So what's the problem?

791
00:54:35.035 --> 00:54:38.739
Even when I'm stuck in a routine,

792
00:54:38.739 --> 00:54:41.889
I'm worried that Jin Ho isn't eating well.

793
00:54:41.889 --> 00:54:45.845
or that you don't feel comfortable alone.

794
00:54:47.952 --> 00:54:50.116
It's heartbreaking.

795
00:54:56.390 --> 00:54:57.757
Have you arrived yet?

796
00:54:57.757 --> 00:54:59.727
You said you wanted to eat meat.

797
00:54:59.727 --> 00:55:02.429
I bought a lot of bacon.

798
00:55:05.269 --> 00:55:07.334
Look at this.

799
00:55:09.203 --> 00:55:11.505
Why weren't you answering the phone?

800
00:55:11.505 --> 00:55:14.144
Today something very good happened to me.

801
00:55:14.144 --> 00:55:16.543
You won't believe it.

802
00:55:18.423 --> 00:55:20.334
Jun Seo,

803
00:55:20.334 --> 00:55:23.963
was with Beom Jun.

804
00:55:23.963 --> 00:55:25.204
It's okay,

805
00:55:25.204 --> 00:55:27.284
I don't get jealous about that anymore.

806
00:55:27.284 --> 00:55:29.657
I'm not angry, it doesn't bother me at all.

807
00:55:29.657 --> 00:55:33.026
Go wash yourself,
The food will be ready when you leave.

808
00:55:42.606 --> 00:55:45.405
I slept with him.

809
00:56:18.138 --> 00:56:21.774
Zero, one, two, seven.

810
00:56:24.882 --> 00:56:28.014
I'll put this in the refrigerator and go out.

811
00:56:37.634 --> 00:56:39.734
I ate too much too fast.

812
00:56:39.734 --> 00:56:42.167
Alright.

813
00:56:42.167 --> 00:56:44.297
What a scare!

814
00:56:51.932 --> 00:56:53.766
Hello.

815
00:57:16.567 --> 00:57:18.331
<i>"Hure."</i>

816
00:57:19.340 --> 00:57:30.070
<i></i>

817
00:57:32.746 --> 00:57:34.651
[<i>Hure</i>, meaning in German]

818
00:57:42.456 --> 00:57:44.891
<i>There are moments like these.</i>

819
00:57:46.961 --> 00:57:49.361
You didn't answer my call, so I went in.

820
00:57:49.361 --> 00:57:52.432
<i>- They hit you out of nowhere.</i>
-Who is she?

821
00:57:54.535 --> 00:57:57.070
<i>They leave you no escape.</i>

822
00:58:03.595 --> 00:58:06.212
What are you talking about?

823
00:58:07.975 --> 00:58:09.783
I'm sorry.

824
00:58:11.915 --> 00:58:14.821
<i>There are moments</i>

825
00:58:15.467 --> 00:58:18.024
<i>in which you do not understand or accept what is happening.</i>

826
00:58:18.662 --> 00:58:20.694
Why do you feel it?

827
00:58:21.295 --> 00:58:24.830
<i>In which there is only darkness and hopelessness.</i>

828
00:58:24.830 --> 00:58:27.967
I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner.

829
00:58:29.670 --> 00:58:32.042
[Whore, prostitute]

830
00:58:32.042 --> 00:58:34.974
<i>In which nothing goes the way you want...</i>

831
00:58:36.347 --> 00:58:39.379
<i>and everything gets out of control.</i>

832
00:58:43.000 --> 00:58:45.620
<i></i>

833
00:58:47.300 --> 00:58:50.423
<i>Now that moment that I know so much...</i>

834
00:58:58.200 --> 00:59:00.834
<i>it reached me again.</i>

835
00:59:03.330 --> 00:59:09.280
<i></i>

836
00:59:09.280 --> 00:59:14.140
<i></i>

837
00:59:14.140 --> 00:59:23.030
<i></i>

